name: Montego Bay Oceanscape 1997
description:
The 40/40 Masterpiece by Phillip Higgins. 

Celebrating over 40 years in Art, only 40 pieces will ever be minted.This piece was painted in 1997.

This is a classic depiction of the beautiful beaches in my country Jamaica.The indigenous people, the Taíno, called it Xaymaca in Arawakan. Meaning the "Land of Wood and Water". 

Oceanscapes are my signature painting expression. My signature pieces have been acclaimed in the tourist & local art industry.
